fields.title: Click it. be ahead
fields.content:
click it. be ahead

Broaden your horizon at the click of a button

We are cosqool, the world’s first English & Arabic-based online tutoring and learning platform with a unique mission.

fields.title: 1/ Are all courses aimed for saudi schools and universities?
fields.content: All of the elementary, middle, and high school courses are specifically made for Saudi Arabian private and public schools. However, University general courses are meant for Saudi and non Saudi Universities.

fields.title: 2/ Which curriculum does the university courses follow?
fields.content: As each univeirty has its own syllabus, we purposely made as many lessons as possible in all of our courses. all you got to do is make your own playlist based on your university syllabus.

fields.title: 3/ Are the test preps in Cosqool Arabic based or English.
fields.content: For now we only have the Arabic version for tahsili and qudrat. However, an English version of both test preps are in the making for the future.

fields.title: 4/ How can I change my grade level?
fields.content: From the moment of your subscription untill the end of the academic year each subscriber will have one free pass to change his grade level for free and it will be renewed every year. If the pass has been already used, a small fee will have to be paid to change the grade level.

fields.title: 5/ Can I have more than one grade level in my subscription?
fields.content: No, you can only add one grade level( from grade 1- university general courses) plus either just one of our test preps or both ( tahsili and qudrat test preps)

fields.title: I greatly appreciate your videos! Not only did I pass Calculus last year with a 96%, but I also discovered my love for the subject - something I had never experienced before truly understanding the mathematical content and the uses of it.
I just found your web site. I am 30 years old and I am now taking up learning where I left off. Thank you so much for all your hard work.

Thank you for your ongoing inspiration. I am a primary school teacher in the north of England and when the conventional education system gets on my nerves, I only need to whack on a Cosqool and my faith in the future of education is restored!

who we are
